p
gcd(b^2-4ac,p)=1
d=b^2-4ac
x=2ak+b
\sum_{0\leq k\leq p-1}\left(\frac{ak^2+bk+c}{p}\right)=\left(\frac{a}{p}\right)
\sum_{0\leq x\leq p-1}\left(\frac{x^2-d}{p}\right)=\left(\frac{4a^2}{p}\right).
\sum_{0\leq x\leq p-1}\left(\frac{x^2-d}{p}\right)=\sum_{0\leq y\leq p-1}(1+\left(\frac{y+d}{p}\right))\left(\frac{y}{p}\right)=\sum_{0\leq y\leq p-1}\left(\frac{y+d}{p}\right)\left(\frac{y}{p}\right)=-1.
\left(\frac{4a^2}{p}\right)
a=1
b=0
c=2
p=3
